quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  21,1,"Mankind’s reckoning has drawn near, while they are in oblivion, disregarding<i>(it) </i>."
  21,2,"No fresh reminder comes to them from their Lord but they listen to it playfully,"
  21,3,"their hearts distracted. And secretly did the unjust converse, “Is this anything but a human being like you<sup>pl </sup>? Will you go along with sorcery while you see?”"
  21,4,"He said{1}, “My Lord knows what is said in the heaven and the earth, for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.”",1:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “Say<sup><small>sg</small></sup>”.]
  21,5,"But they said, “A jumble of dreams; rather, he fabricated it; rather, he is a poet, so let him bring us a sign like those sent to the ancients.”"
  21,6,"None of the towns We annihilated before them had believed. Will they, then, believe?"
  21,7,"And never did We send before you<sup>sg </sup>but men to whom We reveal{1}, so ask the people of the Reminder if you<sup>pl </sup>do not know.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Hafs read it as: “…to whom it is revealed, so ask…”]
  21,8,"And never did We make them a mere body{1},<i>(ones) </i>who eat<sup>pl </sup>no food, for never were they immortal.",1:[A grammatical shift from plural to singular.]
  21,9,"Then We fulfilled the promise to them, so We saved them together with whomever We will{1}, and We annihilated the extremists.",1:[A grammatical shift from past tense to present tense.]
  21,10,"Most surely, We have sent down to you<sup>pl </sup>a Scripture containing your reminder. Do you not reason?"
